A health worker prepares a COVID-19 vaccine. AFP/Diptendu Dutta JOHANNESBURG - South Africa has recorded 15,501 COVID-19 new cases in the last 24 hours. That brings the total number of confirmed cases in the country to 2,090,909. READ: COVID-19 | Gauteng remains epicentre - Health Dept A total of 59,271 tests were conducted in the last 24 hours. A further 457 COVID-19 related deaths have been reported, bringing total fatalities to 61,507 to date.